      <hr>
      <h3>INPUT CONVENTIONS</h3>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Multiple durations</strong> - If more than one playing time is recorded in a note field (5XX), each is coded in a
                     separate occurrence of subfield $a in field 306. If the abbreviation
                        <em>ca.</em> precedes an approximate playing time in a note, this abbreviation is
                     disregarded when recording data in field 306.
         <div class="example">
            <table width="100%">
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
